Discretization Types

	1. Unsupervised
		- Equal Width (Uniform)
			- It is also known as uniform binning
			- we have to decide no.of bins 

				suppose we have this data

				Age
				---
				10
				0
				25
				60
				80
				100
				3
				6

				bins = 10 
				- we simple apply this formula 

				max-min / no.of bins

				so here 

				100-0 / 10

				so there will be 10 bins like this 

				(0-10),(10-20),(20-30).......(90-100)

				we check each value and put it into its corresponding bin

				--------
				| Note |
				--------
					-> It handles outliers
					-> But it struggle with spread of data

				
		- Equal Frequency (Quantile)
		- K-means Binning
